<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">to prevail upon them to bring any to the Fort &#8211; &amp; what little they do bring generally proves to be stinking &amp; scarcely Eatable &#8211; it is not the Living all Winter upon Hares that displeases me, for were they only to bring enough to carry out the Returns &amp; I would be contented<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The said Indian paid 9 skins Credits<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> the other is a Lazy Rascal for he has not yet made a single skin<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 17<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Early this morning sent Martin S<sup>t</sup> André &amp; the Indians for their cache of Meat, gave them 18 hares &amp; a cascamisk<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The hunters brought 93 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="DelHand-author">Wednesday</span> <span class="AddHand-author">Thursday</span> the 1<span class="DelHand-author">8</span><span class="AddHand-author">9</span><sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the forenoon S<sup>t</sup> Cyr &amp; an Indian arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave them drams &amp; tobacco<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they slept 4 nights to come<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  S<sup>t</sup> Cyr is come to go with the Letters to Slave Lake<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e says that the Indians have not yet owing to the cold weather made any skins, but now that the weather is more Moderate they all promise to work the Pichous <span style="text-decoration:underline;">a force</span> &amp; in the spring bring all their Credits<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e is well pleased with his Homme de Loge for I say he gave him plenty of Hares to Eat &#8211; but that La Beccasse is very ill off for if he did not Hunt Hares himself he would starve as his Homme de Loge does not take the least notice of him<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Snowed &amp; Blowed very hard all Day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the morning S<sup>t</sup> Cirs homme de Loge went away<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> he paid 6 skins of Credits &#8211; gave him the Value of 10 skins for having feed S<sup>t</sup> Cir &#8211; &amp; desired him since the others are too great Dogs to give La Becasse wherewith to eat, to take him in Charge &amp; I would pay him well in the spring &#8211; likewise desired him to tell his Parents that if they do not work well &amp; bring all their Credits this Spring &#8211; that I will not for the future give them any more Credits &amp;<sup>c</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon 3 young Men from above arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave them Drams &amp; tobacco, they slept they say 3 nights to come here<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[24]</span></p>

